properties.name: Seh-Changi Mine, Nayband (Neyband), Deyhuk District, Tabas County, South Khorasan Province, Iran
properties.description:
Seh-Changi Mine, Nayband (Neyband), Deyhuk District, Tabas County, South Khorasan Province, Iran

Type: 60

Location: Iran

Abandoned mine in a vein-type lead-zinc deposit. Located northeast of Nayband. Note: "Neyband" appears to be a mis-nomer (from the Handbook of Mineralogy).

properties.description:
Nayband (Neyband), Deyhuk District, Tabas County, South Khorasan Province, Iran

Type: 501

Location: Iran

Nay Band (Persian: ناي بند‎, also Romanized as Nāy Band, Naiband, and Ney Band; also known as Naibandān and Neyban) is a village in Kavir Rural District, Deyhuk District, Tabas County, South Khorasan Province, Iran.
